OL,3,CCharlotte Dujardin given six-month ban
OL,4,Cafter video shows 'error of judgement'
OL,6,FHe acted on behalf of a client who did
OL,7,Fnot wish for the alleged mistreatment
OL,8,Fshown in the video to go unpunished.
OL,10,FThe lawyer, Stephan Wensing, told the
OL,11,Fwebsite: "It is unacceptable that
OL,12,Fdressage sport should be accompanied
OL,13,Fby animal abuse. If top level sport
OL,14,Fcan only be performed in such a way
OL,15,Fthat the welfare of the horse is
OL,16,Fcompromised, then top-level sport
OL,17,Fshould be abolished.
OL,19,F"It is extremely sad that one of the
OL,20,Fmost successful riders in the world
OL,21,Fhas to pay the price. "
